<p><a href=3D"https://mhforce.com/support-item/knm-torque-standard-machine/=
">Torque</a> Explained - In the simplest sense Torque =3D Force * Length</p=
>
<p>Torque is derived and traceable to SI units of length,&nbsp; mass,&nbsp;=
 and time.</p>
<p>The meter is the length of the path&nbsp;traveled&nbsp;by light in a vac=
uum during a time interval of 1/299 792 458 of a second.</p>
<p>The kilogram is the unit of mass; it is equal to the mass of the interna=
tional prototype of the kilogram.</p>
<p>The second is the duration of 9 192 631 770 periods of the radiation cor=
responding to the transition between the two&nbsp;hyper-fine&nbsp;levels of=
 the&nbsp;ground state of the cesium 133 atom.</p>
<p class=3D"image-was-here"><img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" class=
=3D"alignnone size-full wp-image-710" src=3D"https://mhforce.com/wp-content=
/uploads/2017/03/Torque-Definition.png" alt=3D"" width=3D"281" height=3D"21=
9"></p>
<p>Torque Explained</p>
<p>Torque, also called moment or moment of force is the tendency of a force=
 to rotate an object about an axis, fulcrum, or pivot. Just as a force is a=
 push or a pull, a torque can be thought of as a twist.</p>
<p>To convert from one unit of torque to another requires knowing the appro=
priate conversions.</p>
<p>Torque Explained Formulas and Conversions</p>
<p>Torque =3D&nbsp; Force &nbsp;x Length</p>
<p>Force Conversion Factors</p>
<p>newton (N) to lbf =3D MULTIPLY BY &nbsp;0.2248089431</p>
<p>newton (N) to kgf =3D MULTIPLY BY &nbsp;0.1019716212978</p>
<p>newton (N) to&nbsp;ozf&nbsp;=3D MULTIPLY BY 3.59694309</p>
<p>lbf&nbsp;to newton (N) =3D MULTIPLY BY 4.4482216152605</p>
<p>lbf&nbsp;to KGF =3D MULTIPLY BY 0.45359237</p>
<p>lbf&nbsp;to&nbsp;ozf&nbsp; =3D MULTIPLY BY 16</p>
<p>kgf&nbsp;to&nbsp;lbf&nbsp;=3D MULTIPLY BY 2.20462262</p>
<p>kgf&nbsp;to newton (N) =3D MULTIPLY BY 9.80665</p>
<p>Kgf&nbsp;to&nbsp;ozf&nbsp;=3D MULTIPLY BY 35.27396</p>
<p>ozf&nbsp;to newton (N) =3D MULTIPLY BY 0.2780139</p>
<p>ozf&nbsp;to&nbsp;lbf&nbsp;=3D MULTIPLY BY&nbsp;&nbsp;0.0625</p>
<p>ozf&nbsp;to&nbsp;kgf&nbsp;=3D MULTIPLY BY 0.0283495231</p>
<p>Torque =3D &nbsp; Force&nbsp;x&nbsp; Length</p>
<p>Length Conversion Factors</p>
<p>METER (m) to FEET (ft) =3D MULTIPLY BY&nbsp; 3.2808399</p>
<p>METER (m) to INCHES (in) =3D MULTIPLY BY 39.3700787</p>
<p>FEET (ft) to METERS (m) =3D MULTIPLY BY&nbsp; 0.3048</p>
<p>FEET (ft) to INCHES (in) =3D&nbsp;MULTIPLY BY 12</p>
<p>INCHES (in) to FEET (ft)=3D&nbsp;MULTIPLY BY 0.0833333333</p>
<p>INCHES (in) to METERS (m) =3D MULTIPLY BY 0.0254</p>
<p>Examples</p>
<p><em>Force&nbsp; 1N =3D&nbsp;0.2248089431&nbsp;lbf</em><em>&nbsp;</em>&nb=
sp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>Length 1m =3D 3.280839895&=
nbsp;</em><em>ft</em></p>
<p>=E2=80=94<em>=E2=80=941 N-m =3D&nbsp;0.2248089431&nbsp;x 3.280839895 =3D=
&nbsp;0 .7375621489&nbsp; ft-lbf</em></p>
<p><em>Force&nbsp; 1N =3D&nbsp;0.2248089431&nbsp;lbf&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Length 1m =3D 39.3700787 &nbsp; &nbsp;in</em></p>
<p><em>=E2=80=941 N-m =3D&nbsp;0.2248089431&nbsp;x&nbsp;&nbsp; 39.3700787=
=3D&nbsp; 8.50745782 &nbsp;in-lbf</em></p>
